LocalLsdbAddressLessIf.description: The interface index of the interface from which the LSA was received if the interface is unnumbered.

LocalLsdbAge.description: This field is the age of the link state advertisement in seconds.

LocalLsdbChecksum.description: This field is the checksum of the complete contents of the advertisement

LocalLsdbIpAddress.description: The IP address of the interface from which the LSA was received if the interface is numbered.

LocalLsdbLsid.description: The Link State ID is an LS Type Specific field containing a 32-bit identifier in IP address format; it identifies the piece of the routing domain that is being described by the advertisement.

LocalLsdbRouterId.description: The 32-bit number that uniquely identifies the originating router in the Autonomous System.

LocalLsdbSequence.description: The sequence number field is a signed 32-bit integer.  It starts with the value '80000001'h

LocalLsdbType.description: The type of the link state advertisement. Each link state type has a separate advertisement format.
